<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104344">A quick sample of my profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
The AC is probably a bit low, maybe the HPs too, but I am at work so I can't double check. The equipment and resists are correct however.  Yes I know I should be getting my epic, I'm working on it!<br>
<br>
As you can see I have been getting HP gear, and have a pretty (minus a fungi) decent droppable set, but my resists are pretty ordinary.  With SoS proc, my MR hits 77, but I was getting mezzed or slowed a bit in Sebilis, more so with a shammy in the group dishing out HoS (doesn't stack with Major Shielding). Now it seems with the resist changes, my current equipment will be a liability when it comes to resisting slows, ice comets and whatever else those froggies sling at me.<br>
<br>
Has the value of resist gear just gone up big time?  Should the focus for monks equipping themselves with general use droppable gear such as myself switch from chasing HPs big time to finding more balanced equipment?  Will the extra HPs still be the best move? Or is it a case of situational resist equipment use depending on where you have to go?  Early days yet I know, but some initial thoughts would be appreciated.  Should also probably be in the equipment forum, but as the changes are new I think it's probably more important that more people see and voice their opinions.<br>
<br>
Best example I can think of is the Clattering Bone Necklace - did the bonus it gave in hit points just get negated by the resist changes, in favour of the Dragon Tooth Choker?<br>
<br>
Uglukson Umberfists<br>
56 Master<br>
Circle of Sapientia<br>
