<br>
No one has any thoughts on this yet? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udacommon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dacommon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/4/02 7:51:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=306.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resists changes and what it means to the average monk</span><hr size=1> id say we gotta give it a few days, from how people have been talking they screwed up resists on pvp pretty bad, so some of this might have been on accident.<br>
<br>
it seems that real level advantages were supposed to help with this patch, ie droga and dalnir should become easy for 50+ etc.<br>
(easy to get yourself killed there if your not careful)<br>
<br>
if its how they want it, then quite possibly resist gear will become important, id say wait alittle while, at least till after a few emergency patches.<br>
