</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uswysh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swysh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/5/02 1:33:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=306.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resists changes and what it means to the average monk</span><hr size=1> I don't know how rough the changes are yet. I only did some light XP work in Chardok and I resisted far more than normal there but that's not where we're likely to get hurt.<br>
<br>
The only thing I can say about resists is that ever since Hoshkar, I have done whatever it took to put together a 250+(buffed) suit of each resist for situational fights. I considered this part of building a complete character. Just like zone keys and class gear staples. /shrug Granted, this is from a raider's perspective. Well, ex-raider now.<br>
<br>
I'm very glad now that I bothered. Damn DR was tough to come up with pre-FG and group Shaman buffs. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=40638>Swysh's Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kassc>Kassc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/5/02 2:01:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=306.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Resist changes</span><hr size=1> So far from my ventures in Lower Guk, and SolB, resist gear is alot more important now than it was before. Frog and kobold shaman that I could kill with ease and mainly resist most spells thrown at me before are hitting me with their full line now, it's nearly killing me to fight a light blue shaman, and a dark blue..impossible now. If verant doesnt make some changes in the resist during this neverending series of patches, expect resist gear to jump in price dramaticaly.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kassc<br>
52 Monk<br>
Prexus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aganerral>Aganerral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 207<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/5/02 3:51:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=306.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resists changes and what it means to the average monk</span><hr size=1> My guild was in Umbral Plains last night for Doomshade adn Rumblecrush.  The otherm onks and I were getting snared CONSTANTLY by the Dark assassins proc'ing Doming Darkness.  With 155 MR, I resisted maybe 3 out of 10.  From a high blue mob.  This is a bit out of whack, IMHO.  VI should never have fooked with the resist system<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uuglukson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uglukson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/5/02 10:32:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=306.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resists changes and what it means to the average monk</span><hr size=1> Grouped last night in disco in Seb.  Had 132MR with GRM up, resists for fire and cold were in the 110-120 range with druid buffs up, DR &amp; PR around 80-90.<br>
<br>
Shamen were slowing me maybe one cast in 4 with that setup,  whereas I was getting slowed about that rate before with MR at 63.  Still, not as bad as I thought it might be.  Mobs were dispelling a LOT more than usual though, stripping off any resist buffs you might have.  Poison nukes were landing pretty heavily, and disease based DoTs every one in 3 casts.<br>
<br>
Wizzies were nasty, they were landing Entombment of Ice on me 1 in 2 times at that resist level, when they wouldn't touch me with it before with CR at 67.  Ice Comet landed for full probably 1 in every 3 times.<br>
<br>
I had a good group, so we weren't seriously in any danger, but the camp was considerably harder than it used to be due to casters being much more dangerous.  Without the druid buffs, it would have been even more nasty I am sure.  At one stage the 52 cleric overhealed though, got agro and a frog wizzy made short work of here with 2 ICs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umyotis20.showPublicProfile?language=EN>myotis20</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/5/02 11:24:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=306.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://myhome.hanafos.com/~myotis/image/lotusj3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resists changes and what it means to the average monk</span><hr size=1> while I was camping for my alt druid's for corrupted goblin in Lake Rathetear, it seems you get nuked by full amount even by green mobs if you don't gear up with rez gears/buffs..<br>
<br>
getting continuously nuked for 300's at lev 60 is not only embarassing but pretty much life threatening :P. I think what VI intended in first place was actually the opposite of what is happening now.<br>
<br>
I can't imagine myself entering Droga now with all those casters/sk's chain nuking/HTing me. no more faction fix for me *sigh*  <p>Maitri Modestferret<br>Grand Master, Jain Sadhvi<br>
Sha`Dezar of E'ci<br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umyotis20.showPublicProfile?language=EN>myotis20</A> at: 9/5/02 11:26:25 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukunismarfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kunis Marfury</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/6/02 9:51:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=306.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resists changes and what it means to the average monk</span><hr size=1> if they don't change the resist as it is now, they should add more reists on items.<br>
getting resist gear below lvl 50 is a pain and even after if you are not in a big guild :/ <p><p align=center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=295712><img src=http://kunis.marfury.free.fr/kunis/signature/kunis.marfury_0.jpg border=0 title ="my magelo... like everyone"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utakuansoho.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Takuan Soho</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://freespace.virgin.net/samurai.london/master.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/6/02 10:30:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=306.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> FG</span><hr size=1> Did anyone else notice this? <br>
The mushrooms in FG land their slow and stun a lot lot more than before. I left in disgust after seeing how well they were upgraded and went for a game of counter strike. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/useriph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seriph</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 262<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/7/02 5:04:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=306.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FG</span><hr size=1> The day after the patch, I went to seb and hopped in a group that was just forming for crypt.  We went past bugs and the first 2 frogs we came to at the beginning of the tunnel were shaman.  I pulled them both thinking nothing of the resistance changes.  I was immediately Malosini'd or whatever they cast, slowed, double DoTed, and continuously nuked to hell.  I managed to resist maybe 1 or 2 nukes during the fight and got down to 7% hp a few times.  Before the patch, I could have soloed both of these at the same time.  This made me furious.  We came to the entrance to crypt and there was a knight and enchanter guarding it.  I pulled them both again figuring that my MR was decent and chanters never got anything on me...Sure enough, I was tashed and charmed before the chanter got back to the group.  I stayed charmed the entire time till both mobs were killed.<br>
<br>
